<!-- 10 TIPS -->
<section class="tips-section">
  <div class="tips-inner">
    <div class="section-label" style="color:var(--sienna)">From experience</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color:var(--cream); margin-bottom:0;">10 tips for a smooth relocation</h2>
    <div class="tips-grid">
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num">1</div>
        <div><div class="tip-title">Start the home search early</div><div class="tip-body">Begin 3–4 months before your start date. Physician and professional schedules are demanding — give yourself runway.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num">2</div>
        <div><div class="tip-title">Prioritize schools first</div><div class="tip-body">Then find neighborhoods that match. Schools drive everything for families and affect resale value more than almost any other factor.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num">3</div>
        <div><div class="tip-title">Get pre-approved early</div><div class="tip-body">You can qualify with just an employment contract. Physician loan programs allow 0% down with no PMI — ask me about lenders who specialize in this.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num">4</div>
        <div><div class="tip-title">Consider renting first if timing is tight</div><div class="tip-body">A 6–12 month rental lets you buy without pressure after settling in and getting a real feel for neighborhoods.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num">5</div>
        <div><div class="tip-title">Visit in person if possible</div><div class="tip-body">Photos don't capture the feel of a neighborhood. I offer a personal community tour — I'll drive you through every area on your shortlist.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num">6</div>
        <div><div class="tip-title">Think about your spouse's needs</div><div class="tip-body">Career, community, cultural fit, proximity to family — these matter as much as the work location. I experienced this firsthand.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num">7</div>
        <div><div class="tip-title">Find the community within the community</div><div class="tip-body">Cultural and social fit matters deeply. I can connect you to South Asian networks, professional groups, and community events before you land.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num">8</div>
        <div><div class="tip-title">Don't underestimate commute time</div><div class="tip-body">Sacramento traffic is mild compared to the Bay Area, but test the actual drive from target neighborhoods to your workplace on a weekday morning.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num">9</div>
        <div><div class="tip-title">Build your support network early</div><div class="tip-body">Demanding careers mean your partner needs friends, community, and resources nearby. Don't wait until you arrive to start building connections.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num">10</div>
        <div><div class="tip-title">Use an agent who truly gets it</div><div class="tip-body">There's a difference between an agent who serves relocating families and one who has lived this journey. I've done both.</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

